import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Load US states shapefile
    states = gpd.read_file("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json")

    # Count cities per state
    city_counts = data.groupby('state').size().reset_index(name='city_count')

    # Merge city counts with states shapefile
    states = states.merge(city_counts, left_on='name', right_on='state')

    # Create choropleth map
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(12, 6))
    divider = make_axes_locatable(ax)
    cax = divider.append_axes("right", size="5%", pad=0.1)
    states.plot(column='city_count', ax=ax, legend=True, cax=cax, cmap='viridis', edgecolor='black')

    # Set title and legend
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities across states?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_axis_off()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['vowel_count'], bins='auto', color='blue', alpha=0.7, rwidth=0.85)
    plt.xlabel('Vowel Count')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of vowel counts in city names?', wrap=True)
    plt.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.75)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    first_letter_counts = data['first_letter'].value_counts()
    first_letter_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='c', edgecolor='k')
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of first letters in city names?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('First Letters')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(['First Letters'], loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
